FeedPackage.Description: This package allows Bundles to be created using files from Azure. The Bundles can be either CSS or JS Bundles that are minified and a seperate Gzip compressed file will be created as well. It sets the CdnPath of the Bundle to the compressed file if the Request Accepts gzip. Otherwise the CdnPath is set to the non-compressed file. The bundle is also created in memory for complete fallback protection.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: There are 5 setting values that can be set in either the config file or the web.config file of your website. AzureAccountName(string) - Your Azure Account Name. AzureAccessKey(string) - Your Access Key. CdnPath(string) - Url for your blob storage. CachePollTime(int) - Poll time for custom cache dependency. BundleCacheTTL(int) - max-age to cache bundle.
FeedPackage.Summary: Requires an Azure Storage account.
FeedPackage.Tags: Azure Bundling Gzip
FeedPackage.Title: Tadabase
